bib_record.title: Quasi-elastic scattering and transfer angular distribution for 10,11B+232Th systems at near-barrier energies

free_txt: 14UD Pelletron
Four silicon surface barrier
detector telescope with different thicknesses: T1
with delta E=25 um and E=300 um T2 with delta E=40 um
and E=300 um T3 with delta E=25 um and E=300 um T4
with delta E=25 um and E=300 um All four telescopes
were mounted at a distance of 21.1 cm from target,
having a front collimator of 6 mm, which imposes an
angular uncertainty of +-0.81 degree.
Two monitor detectors with thickness around
300 um, were mounted at 65 cm from target, with 1 mm
collimator, at fixed angles of +/- 18 degree with
respect to beam direction for absolute normalization
and beam monitoring.
